problems.title: Determine Zodiac Sign and Compatibility
problems.description:
Given birth dates of two people, determine their zodiac signs and compatibility.

Zodiac signs (by month and day):
- Aries: March 21 - April 19
- Taurus: April 20 - May 20
- Gemini: May 21 - June 20
- Cancer: June 21 - July 22
- Leo: July 23 - August 22
- Virgo: August 23 - September 22
- Libra: September 23 - October 22
- Scorpio: October 23 - November 21
- Sagittarius: November 22 - December 21
- Capricorn: December 22 - January 19
- Aquarius: January 20 - February 18
- Pisces: February 19 - March 20

Compatibility:
- Fire signs (Aries, Leo, Sagittarius) compatible with Air (Gemini, Libra, Aquarius)
- Water signs (Cancer, Scorpio, Pisces) compatible with Earth (Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn)
- Same element: "Very Compatible"
- Compatible element: "Compatible"
- Otherwise: "Not Compatible"

Print:
- First person's sign
- Second person's sign
- Compatibility

Input Format:
First line: day1 month1
Second line: day2 month2

Output Format:
Print three lines: sign1, sign2, compatibility
problems.examples:
Sample Input
15 3
20 4

Sample Output
Pisces
Aries
Not Compatible

Sample Input
5 8
10 11

Sample Output
Leo
Scorpio
Not Compatible

Sample Input
1 6
15 9

Sample Output
Gemini
Virgo
Compatible

Explanation:
Determine signs using date ranges with careful boundary handling, then check element compatibility using nested conditions.
hintsList: Use nested if-else to determine sign based on month and day ranges. Then map signs to elements (Fire/Water/Earth/Air), and check compatibility using element matching.
